# Testing lot disposal scenarios.

# * Lot disposal

# ** 1. Simple dispose - negative amount to Asset account with cost basis - gets ptype:dispose tag
<
2026-01-01 Buy stock
    assets:broker    5 AAPL {$100} @ $100
    assets:cash

2026-01-02 Sell stock
    assets:broker    -5 AAPL {$100} @ $100
    assets:cash       $500

$ hledger -f- print --verbose-tags
2026-01-01 Buy stock
    assets:broker                                  5 AAPL {$100} @ $100  ; ptype: acquire
    assets:cash

2026-01-02 Sell stock
    assets:broker                                 -5 AAPL {$100} @ $100  ; ptype: dispose
    assets:cash                                 $500

>=

# ** 2. Simple single-lot disposal: the sell posting selects the appropriate lot subaccount.
<
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell
    assets:stocks    -5 AAPL {$50} @ $50
    assets:cash       $250

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots -N
              5 AAPL  assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}

# ** 3. Full lot consumption: the lot is fully consumed.
<
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell all
    assets:stocks   -10 AAPL {$50} @ $50
    assets:cash       $500

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots -N

# ** 4. FIFO multi-lot disposal: sell with {} can select multiple lots, oldest first.
<
2026-01-15 buy cheap
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 buy expensive
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$60}
    assets:checking

2026-03-01 sell some
    assets:stocks   -15 AAPL {} @ $55
    assets:cash      $825
    revenue:gains   -$25

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots -N
              5 AAPL  assets:stocks:{2026-02-01, $60}

# ** 5. Insufficient lots error: disposing more than is available at the specified cost fails.
<
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell too many
    assets:stocks   -15 AAPL {$50} @ $55
    assets:cash      $825

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots
>2 /insufficient lots/
>=1

# ** 6. Disposing when there's no lots at all gives a different error, apparently. ?
<
2026-02-01 sell without buying
    assets:stocks    -5 AAPL {$50} @ $55
    assets:cash       $275

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots
>2 /no lots available/
>=1

# ** 7. Multiple disposals reduce lots correctly.
<
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell some
    assets:stocks    -3 AAPL {$50} @ $50
    assets:cash       $150

2026-02-15 sell more
    assets:stocks    -4 AAPL {$50} @ $50
    assets:cash       $200

2026-03-01 sell rest
    assets:stocks    -3 AAPL {$50} @ $50
    assets:cash       $150

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots -N

# ** 8. A dispose posting with unknown transacted cost (selling price) is an error.
<
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell
    assets:stocks    -5 AAPL {$50}
    assets:cash

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots
>2 /no transacted price/
>=1

# ** 9. Explicit lot subaccount on dispose posting is accepted when it matches the resolved lot.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {} @ $50
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}    -5 AAPL {2026-01-15, $50} @ $60
    assets:cash      $300
    revenue:gains   -$50

$ hledger -f- print --lots
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}               10 AAPL {} @ $50
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}               -5 AAPL {2026-01-15, $50} @ $60
    assets:cash                                 $300
    revenue:gains                               $-50
    equity:unrealised-gain                       $50

>=

# ** 10. Explicit lot subaccount that doesn't match the resolved lot is an error.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {} @ $50
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell
    assets:stocks:{2026-02-01, $99}    -5 AAPL {2026-01-15, $50} @ $60
    assets:cash      $300
    revenue:gains   -$50

$ hledger -f- print --lots
>2 /conflicting cost basis date/
>=1

# ** 11. Implicit multi-lot disposal: bare negative amount with no cost basis, sale price inferred from cash.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:
2026-01-15 buy cheap
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {} @ $50
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 buy expensive
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {} @ $55
    assets:checking

2026-03-01 sell some
    assets:stocks   -15 AAPL
    assets:cash      $900

$ hledger -f- print --lots -x desc:sell
2026-03-01 sell some
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}              -10 AAPL {2026-01-15, $50} @ $60
    assets:stocks:{2026-02-01, $55}               -5 AAPL {2026-02-01, $55} @ $60
    assets:cash                                 $900
    revenues:gain                              $-125
    equity:unrealised-gain                      $125

>=

# ** 12. Implicit multi-lot disposal: negative amount with explicit @ cost, cash and gains inferred.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:
2026-01-15 buy cheap
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {} @ $50
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 buy expensive
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {} @ $55
    assets:checking

2026-03-01 sell
    assets:stocks   -15 AAPL @ $60
    assets:cash

$ hledger -f- print --lots -x desc:sell
2026-03-01 sell
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}              -10 AAPL {2026-01-15, $50} @ $60
    assets:stocks:{2026-02-01, $55}               -5 AAPL {2026-02-01, $55} @ $60
    assets:cash                                 $900
    revenues:gain                              $-125
    equity:unrealised-gain                      $125

>=

# ** 13. Plain print (no --lots) on a multi-lot disposal collapses the per-lot
# split back to the user's single original posting.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:
2026-01-15 buy cheap
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {} @ $50
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 buy expensive
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {} @ $55
    assets:checking

2026-03-01 sell
    assets:stocks   -15 AAPL @ $60
    assets:cash

$ hledger -f- print desc:sell
2026-03-01 sell
    assets:stocks                                -15 AAPL @ $60
    assets:cash
    revenues:gain                              $-125
    equity:unrealised-gain                      $125

>=

# ** 14. print -x on the same disposal also collapses (cost basis annotations
# stripped because the user didn't write one), but fills in inferred amounts.
$ hledger -f- print -x desc:sell
2026-03-01 sell
    assets:stocks                                -15 AAPL @ $60
    assets:cash                                 $900
    revenues:gain                              $-125
    equity:unrealised-gain                      $125

>=

# ** 15. print --lots on the same disposal shows the per-lot split with lot
# subaccounts but keeps the user's amount form (no inferred cost basis details).
$ hledger -f- print --lots desc:sell
2026-03-01 sell
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}              -10 AAPL @ $60
    assets:stocks:{2026-02-01, $55}               -5 AAPL @ $60
    assets:cash
    revenues:gain                              $-125
    equity:unrealised-gain                      $125

>=

# ** 16. Bare negative lotful posting without selling price gets a lot subaccount
# (dispose matches lot via FIFO, no gain posting since there's no selling price).
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:

2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:cash

2026-02-01 gift given
    assets:stocks    -5 AAPL
    equity:opening

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots -N
              5 AAPL  assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}

# ** 17. Balance assertion on a multi-lot disposal is moved to a generated parent-account
# posting with subaccount-inclusive checking (=*), so the assertion still passes on re-read.

<
2026-01-15 buy cheap
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 buy expensive
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$60}
    assets:checking

2026-03-01 sell all
    assets:stocks    -20 AAPL {} @ $70 = 0 AAPL
    assets:cash       $1400

$ hledger -f- print --lots -x desc:sell
2026-03-01 sell all
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}              -10 AAPL {2026-01-15, $50} @ $70
    assets:stocks:{2026-02-01, $60}              -10 AAPL {2026-02-01, $60} @ $70
    assets:stocks                                  0 AAPL                         =* 0 AAPL
    assets:cash                                $1400
    revenues:gain                              $-300
    equity:unrealised-gain                      $300

>=

# ** 18. A balance assertion on a dispose posting is moved to a generated parent-account
# posting with subaccount-inclusive checking (=*).
# Here after selling lot1, assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50} is 0 but assets:stocks:{2026-02-01, $60} is 10 AAPL.
# The assertion = 10 AAPL, converted to =*, checks the inclusive balance of assets:stocks = 10 AAPL.
<
2026-01-15 buy lot1
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 buy lot2
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$60}
    assets:checking

2026-03-01 sell lot1
    assets:stocks    -10 AAPL {} @ $70 = 10 AAPL
    assets:cash       $700

$ hledger -f- --lots check assertions

# ** 19. But if a lot subaccount is written explicitly, a balance assertion checks that subaccount's balance.
<
2026-01-15 buy lot1
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}    10 AAPL
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 buy lot2
    assets:stocks:{2026-02-01, $60}    10 AAPL
    assets:checking

2026-03-01 sell lot1
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}    -10 AAPL = 0 AAPL
    assets:cash       $700

$ hledger -f- check assertions

# ** 20. Round-trip: print --lots -x output can be re-read and balance assertions still pass.
# A generated parent account posting with a =* assertion reproduces the original assertion's meaning.
<
2026-01-15 buy cheap
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 buy expensive
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$60}
    assets:checking

2026-03-01 sell all
    assets:stocks    -20 AAPL {} @ $70 = 0 AAPL
    assets:cash       $1400

$ hledger -f- print --lots -x | hledger -f- check assertions

# ** 21. Dispose with explicit lot subaccount infers cost basis from account name.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:cash

2026-02-01 sell with explicit lot subaccount
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}    -5 AAPL @ $60
    assets:cash

$ hledger -f- print --lots -x desc:sell
2026-02-01 sell with explicit lot subaccount
    assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}               -5 AAPL {2026-01-15, $50} @ $60
    assets:cash                                 $300
    revenues:gain                               $-50
    equity:unrealised-gain                       $50

>=

# ** 22. Insufficient lots error shows reduction method.
<
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell too many
    assets:stocks   -15 AAPL {$50} @ $55
    assets:cash      $825

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots
>2 /Using FIFO \(default\)/
>=1

# ** 23. Insufficient lots error shows review hint.
<
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell too many
    assets:stocks   -15 AAPL {$50} @ $55
    assets:cash      $825

$ hledger -f- check
>2 /need 15 but only 10 available/
>=1

# ** 24. No lots available error shows commodity tag as method source.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots: LIFO

2026-02-01 sell without buying
    assets:stocks    -5 AAPL {$50} @ $55
    assets:cash       $275

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots
>2 /Using LIFO \(from commodity tag on AAPL\)/
>=1

# ** 25. Error shows account tag as method source.
<
account assets:stocks  ; lots: LIFO

2026-02-01 sell without buying
    assets:stocks    -5 AAPL {$50} @ $55
    assets:cash       $275

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots
>2 /Using LIFO \(from account tag on assets:stocks\)/
>=1

# ** 26. Lot error highlights the posting line, not the transaction line.
<
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:checking

2026-02-01 sell too many
    assets:stocks   -15 AAPL {$50} @ $55
    assets:cash      $825

$ hledger -f- bal assets:stocks --lots
>2 /6 \|     assets:stocks/
>=1

# ** 27. Expense posting with cost basis does not get a lot subaccount.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$80}
    assets:cash

2026-02-01 sell with stock fee
    assets:stocks    -5 AAPL {$80} @ $90
    expenses:fees    0.1 AAPL {$80} @ $90
    assets:cash      $441
    revenue:gains   -$49

$ hledger -f- bal --lots -N
               $-359  assets:cash
            5.0 AAPL  assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $80}
                 $49  equity:unrealised-gain
            0.1 AAPL  expenses:fees
                $-49  revenue:gains

# ** 28. Sub-cent gain (issue #2575): a fractional-commodity disposal
# produces a gain below 2-decimal display precision. The dispose entry has
# no top-level $ amounts (only ETH), so entry-local $ precision is 0 dp;
# the inferred gain is rounded to integer $ ($0 / $0) per the
# precision-tolerance rule. Sub-cent gains in 0-dp entries are rounded
# away — users who want sub-cent resolution should record cents-bearing
# amounts explicitly in the entry.
<
commodity 1.000000 ETH  ; lots:
2026-03-06 buy
    assets:custodial      1.000000 ETH
    assets:custodial    $-1,980.78

2026-03-09 transfer
    assets:custodial        -1.000000 ETH
    assets:cold wallet       0.999601 ETH
    expenses:fees:trading    0.000399 ETH @ $1,992.36

$ hledger -f- print -x --lots desc:transfer
2026-03-09 transfer
    assets:custodial:{2026-03-06, $1,980.78}      -0.999601 ETH {2026-03-06, $1,980.78}
    assets:custodial:{2026-03-06, $1,980.78}      -0.000399 ETH {2026-03-06, $1,980.78} @ $1,992.36
    assets:cold wallet:{2026-03-06, $1,980.78}     0.999601 ETH {2026-03-06, $1,980.78}
    expenses:fees:trading                          0.000399 ETH @ $1,992.36
    revenues:gain                                 $0
    equity:unrealised-gain                        $0

>=

# ** 29. Disposal balance check works with --infer-equity.
# Equity conversion postings (from --infer-equity) should not disrupt the
# disposal cost-basis balance check, and should not carry cost basis annotations.
<
account income:capital  ; type:G

2026-01-15 buy
    assets:broker    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:cash

2026-02-15 sell
    assets:cash       $600
    assets:broker    -10 AAPL {$50} @ $60
    income:capital   -$100

$ hledger -f- print --lots --infer-equity
2026-01-15 buy
    assets:broker:{2026-01-15, $50}               10 AAPL {$50}
    equity:conversion:$-AAPL:AAPL                -10 AAPL
    equity:conversion:$-AAPL:$                  $500
    assets:cash

2026-02-15 sell
    assets:cash                                 $600
    assets:broker:{2026-01-15, $50}              -10 AAPL {$50} @ $60
    equity:conversion:$-AAPL:AAPL                 10 AAPL
    equity:conversion:$-AAPL:$                 $-600
    income:capital                             $-100
    equity:unrealised-gain                      $100

>=

# ** 30. Equity conversion amounts are rounded to the transaction's local display precision.
# 9.216 * 1801.215277778 = 16600.000000002, which should be rounded to 16600.00 (2dp from Rs-16600.00).
<
2017-04-09 buy
    assets:fund    9.216 FUND @ Rs1801.215277778
    assets:cash                       Rs-16600.00

$ hledger -f- print --infer-equity
2017-04-09 buy
    assets:fund                                    9.216 FUND @ Rs1801.215277778
    equity:conversion:FUND-Rs:FUND                -9.216 FUND
    equity:conversion:FUND-Rs:Rs             Rs16600.00
    assets:cash                             Rs-16600.00

>=

# ** 31. Unbalanced disposal error shows per-posting cost-basis breakdown.
<
account income:capital  ; type:G
commodity FUND  ; lots:

2026-01-15 buy
    assets:fund    10 FUND {Rs100}
    assets:savings            Rs-1000

2026-02-15 sell
    assets:savings                             Rs1500
    assets:fund    -10 FUND {Rs100} @@ Rs1500
    income:capital                             Rs-400

$ hledger -f- print --lots
>2 /realised gain amount is wrong/
>=1

# ** 32. An imprecise per-unit cost basis produces sub-Rs0.005 noise in
# calculated gain. The user-written rgain matches at the entry's local
# Rs precision (2 dp), so it is accepted and the entry is balanced.
# 9.216 × 1801.215277778 = 16600.000000002, off by 0.000000002 from the
# Rs16600.00 paid; this rounds away at the entry's 2 dp tolerance.
<
account income:capital  ; type:G

2017-04-09 buy
    assets:fund    9.216 FUND {Rs1801.215277778}
    assets:savings                   Rs-16600.00

2019-07-10 sell
    assets:savings                                     Rs19403.24
    assets:fund    -9.216 FUND {Rs1801.215277778} @@ Rs19403.24
    income:capital                                     Rs-2803.24

$ hledger -f- print --lots
2017-04-09 buy
    assets:fund:{2017-04-09, Rs1801.215277778}         9.216 FUND {Rs1801.215277778}
    assets:savings                              Rs-16600.00

2019-07-10 sell
    assets:savings                              Rs19403.24
    assets:fund:{2017-04-09, Rs1801.215277778}       -9.216 FUND {Rs1801.215277778} @@ Rs19403.24
    income:capital                              Rs-2803.24
    equity:unrealised-gain                       Rs2803.24

>=

# ** 33. TODO: {{ }} total cost basis syntax should let us work around test
# 25's imprecision issue. But currently hledger normalises {{ total }} to
# { per-unit } internally, and this normalisation is flawed:
#
#   - It divides the total by the posting's *signed* quantity. So the acquire's
#     9.216 FUND {{Rs16600.00}} stores per-unit Rs1801.22 but the dispose's
#     -9.216 FUND {{Rs16600.00}} is normalised to per-unit Rs-1801.22 (wrong sign),
#     and the dispose fails to match the acquired lot.
#
#   - It rounds the per-unit to the commodity's declared precision (2 decimals
#     for Rs), so even with the sign fixed, Rs1801.22 would not equal the
#     acquire's exact Rs16600/9.216 ≈ Rs1801.215277778..., and the Decimal
#     artifact from test 25 would reappear.
#
# Until this is fixed, users have to avoid test 25's case by choosing
# quantities and per-unit costs that multiply exactly.
<
account income:capital  ; type:G

2017-04-09 buy
    assets:fund    9.216 FUND {{Rs16600.00}}
    assets:savings                   Rs-16600.00

2019-07-10 sell
    assets:savings                                     Rs19403.24
    assets:fund    -9.216 FUND {{Rs16600.00}} @@ Rs19403.24
    income:capital                                     Rs-2803.24

$ hledger -f- print --lots
>2 /no lots available for commodity FUND in account assets:fund/
>=1

